<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-11-15T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-11-15T07:00:00-05:00" n="629" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5431/97: Telegram (part
                                air)</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Williamson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-11-15T13:00:00+01:00">November 15, 1934—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 17—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>42. Department’s 67, November 14, 7 p.m. Swiss Department of Public
                                Economy has already on more than one occasion strongly advised
                                against Swiss business interests making proposed <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi> on December 17. While it of course cannot prevent
                                departure to the United States of Swiss citizens it will reiterate
                                its position through official and semiofficial bodies such as
                                Chambers of Commerce.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Williamson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>